<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-05-22T11:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-05-22T11:00:00-05:00" n="294" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d294">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 657.119/455</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss>
                                    to the Minister in Norway</hi> (<persName corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_SAG1" type="to"><hi rend="italic">Schmedeman</hi></persName>)</head>
                            <opener>
                                <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                            </opener>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-05-22T12:00:00-04:00">
                                        <hi rend="italic">May 22, 1918, noon.</hi>
                                    </date>
                                </dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>324. For <persName corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_DAV1">Dye</persName>
                                [from War Trade Board]:</p>
                            <p>No. 8. Your No. 1, Legation 727, May 15, 7 p.m.<note n="1" xml:id="d294fn1">Not printed.</note> We will adopt the procedure
                                which you state has been adopted by British and which involves
                                issuing export licenses against certificates issued by associations
                                prior to May 10, provided associations confirm these in writing to
                                Allied Trade Committee. You will obtain from associations already
                                organized a written declaration that until new agreements can be
                                negotiated they will consider their former agreements <pb facs="0353" n="1187" xml:id="pg_1187"/> with Great Britain as
                                applicable to imports from United States, subject, however, to such
                                modifications as are necessitated by the terms of the recently
                                concluded commercial agreement.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <persName corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_LR1">
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Lansing</hi>
                                    </persName>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>